    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <U>Starting</U> : bid 0, 1 or 2. The best is not to start so you play on your sites<br />
<br />
<U>Fellowship part :</U><br />
<B>Gandalf</B> : he is here to draw card at the start of your fellowship phase, cancel the skirmish with his staff, slim the twilight pool with glamdring, and play servant of secret fire to low opponent power, and discard condition with Sleep Caradhras<br />
<br />
<B>Aragorn</B> : he&#39;s the most important character in your deck, because he heal on of your character at the start of your fellowship phase, he is very powerfull with ranger sword and flaming brand, and saga of elendil : 11 or 14 damage+1, and he is an archer with aragorn bow<br />
<br />
<B>Boromir</B> : he is here to fight Uruk and also to be killed if you&#39;ve only this solution<br />
<br />
<B>Legolas</B> : he an other important character of your deck, if you are at a river or a forest : 2 archery wound, with long knives and bow of galadhrim he is a fighter so use servant with him and he&#39;ll be a killing machine.<br />
<br />
<b>Albert Dreary</b> : he is here to discard some part of the moria and uruk&#39;s conditions.<br />
<br />
<U>Shadow part :</U><br />
<br />
<B>Ulaire Cantea</B> : can discard weapon, and will take archery snipers wound.<br />
<br />
<B>Ulaire Nerta</B> : if the fellowship is too big : slim it with other nazgul<br />
<br />
<B>Ulaire Neyla</B> : 2 wound or 2 burdens, it&#39;s too easy to spot so you have a 10 fierce damage+1 , use him with some black steed and nazgul sword : <B>KILLING MACHINE</B><br />
<br />
<B>Ulaire Enquea</B> : 6 compagion or 5 burdens => 3 wounds : too cool<br />
<br />
<B>The Witch King</B> : he&#39;s the KING.<br />
<br />
<B>Wreathed in Shadow</B> : to slim the archery phase<br />
<br />
<B>Blade Tip and Blade Tip</> : use them on the same character : it&#39;s poison => NICE<br />
<br />
<U>Common Part</U><br />
<br />
Don&#39;t forget : never never double move : your opponent should play on your site.<br />
<br />
<br />
